reference.partintro:


 &reftitle.intro;


  PDO_IBM is a driver that implements the PHP Data
  Objects (PDO) interface to enable access from PHP to IBM databases.




&reference.pdo-ibm.configure;

refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.examples;
PDO_IBM DSN example using db2cli.ini
The following example shows a PDO_IBM DSN for connecting to an DB2 database cataloged as DB2_9 in db2cli.ini:
$db = new PDO("ibm:DSN=DB2_9", "", "");
[DB2_9] Database=testdb Protocol=tcpip Hostname=11.22.33.444 Servicename=56789
PDO_IBM DSN example using a connection string
The following example shows a PDO_IBM DSN for connecting to an DB2 database named testdb using the DB2 CLI connection string syntax.
$db = new PDO("ibm:DRIVER={IBM DB2 ODBC DRIVER};DATABASE=testdb;" . "HOSTNAME=11.22.33.444;PORT=56789;PROTOCOL=TCPIP;", "testuser", "tespass");
